@dgsb ahh, I think I found it, haha. We're also adding a field `"func"`, and it's just colliding when I've used the text formatter. This is also weird though, because I see the prefixing code should handle this.. but I've got this simple example failing locally with latest logrus code go1.11.1, darwin.

```
package main

import (
	"github.com/sirupsen/logrus"
)

func main() {
	log := logrus.New()
	log.WithField("func", "whatever!").Info("hello")
}
```

Found the|my issue. Field "file" has a special behavior (since commit 251d6bf71382da18d56ae619e48a8404728b40b0 ?)

This code:
```
package main
import (
    "github.com/sirupsen/logrus"
)

func main() {

 initLog := logrus.New();

 initLog.WithFields(logrus.Fields{
        "file": "Hello Word",
 }).Warn("Hell");

 for {
 }
}
```

successfully work with 
$ go build && ./test

but fail with 
$ go build && nohup ./test

